member.summary:
A convention that configures the default model  as
 for newer PostgreSQL versions,
and  for pre-10.0 versions.

Returns the collation to be used for the column - including the PostgreSQL-specific default column
collation defined at the model level (see
).

example.code:
[StringFormatMethod("message")]
void ShowError(string message, params object[] args) { /* do something */ }

void Foo() {
  ShowError("Failed: {0}"); // Warning: Non-existing argument in format string
}

